Porto, Benfica, Braga, Villarreal Advance to Europa League Semifinals

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-14T20:59:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/porto-benfica-braga-villarreal-advance-to-europa-league-semifinals.html
Porto and Villarreal won to advance
to the Europa League soccer semifinals, as Benfica and Braga
progressed with draws.  Porto beat Spartak Moscow 5-2 to complete a 10-3 victory
over the two-game quarterfinal. Villarreal’s 3-1 win at FC
Twente gave it a 8-2 overall victory.  Braga’s goalless home draw with Dynamo Kiev sent it through
on the away-goals rule following a 1-1 tie in  Ukraine  last week.
Benfica drew 2-2 at  PSV Eindhoven  to advance 6-3.  Porto meets Villarreal and Braga faces Benfica in the two-
match semifinals, which will be played April 28 and May 5. The
final is May 18 in Dublin.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  